through the\nFinancing SPV, a Loan and Security Agreement by and among the Company, the Financing SPV, JPMorgan Chase Bank, National Association, as lender and administrative agent for the lender parties providing for a senior secured revolving credit facility\nto the Financing SPV of $200\xa0million (the JPM Facility). The JPM Facility size is increasable to up to $800\xa0million subject to the satisfaction of various conditions, including availability under the borrowing base, which is\nbased on a combination of unfunded Capital Commitments and other loan collateral including the Financing SPVs portfolio investments. 26North Direct Lending LP serves as the portfolio manager under the JPM Facility (in such capacity, the\nFacility Portfolio Manager). U.S. Bank Trust Company National Association serves as collateral agent and U.S. Bank National Association serves as securities intermediary. Proceeds from borrowings under the JPM Facility are to be used to\nfacilitate investments and for the timely payment of the Financing SPVs expenses, and to make certain permitted distributions to the Company.\n120\nTable of Contents\nThe JPM Facility is a revolving credit facility with a revolving period ending October\xa018, 2026 (or\nupon the occurrence of certain events as specified therein) and has a scheduled maturity date of October\xa018, 2028. Advances under the JPM Facility are available in U.S. dollars and other permitted currencies. The interest charged on the JPM\nFacility is based on SOFR, SONIA, SARON, EURIBOR or CDOR, as applicable (or, if SOFR is not available, a benchmark replacement or a base rate (which is the greater of the prime rate and the federal funds rate plus 0.50%), as applicable),\nplus a margin of (1) 2.75% prior to the earlier of (x)\xa0the first day on which the Company has drawn more than one-third of its Capital Commitments and (y)\xa0April\xa018, 2025 and (2) 2.85%\nthereafter. Under the JPM Facility, the Financing SPV will pay an undrawn fee of (i)\xa0during the first nine months of the JPM Facility, 0.50% per annum and (ii)\xa0thereafter, 0.75% per annum, in each case, on the average daily unused amount\nof the financing commitments until the end of the revolving period, subject to minimum utilization requirements.\nThe obligations of the Financing SPV to\nthe lenders under the JPM Facility are secured by a first priority security interest in the unfunded Capital Commitments to the Company and the related proceeds and all of the Financing SPVs portfolio investments and other assets.\nIn connection with the JPM Facility, the Financing SPV has made certain customary representations and warranties and is required to comply with various\ncovenants, reporting requirements and other customary requirements for similar facilities. The JPM Facility contains customary events of default for similar financing transactions, including if a change of control of the Financing SPV occurs. Upon\nthe occurrence and during the continuation of an event of default, the lenders under the JPM Facility may declare the outstanding advances and all other obligations under the JPM Facility immediately due and payable. The occurrence of an event of\ndefault (as described above) triggers a requirement that the Financing SPV obtain the consent of the lenders under the applicable JPM Facility prior to entering into any sale or disposition with respect to portfolio investments.\nAs of December\xa031, 2023, to the Companys knowledge, each of the Company, the Financing SPV and the Facility Portfolio Manager was in compliance\nwith all covenants and other requirements applicable to it under the JPM Facility.\n7. Wrubel, a Class\xa0III Director of the Company, informed the Board of his resignation as a member of the Board, a member of\nthe Audit Committee and a member and Chairperson of the Nominating and Governance Committee, effective the same day upon acceptance by the Board. Mr.\xa0Wrubels resignation was not due to a disagreement with the Company on any matter\nrelating to its operations, policies, or practices. The Board accepted Mr.\xa0Wrubels resignation at a meeting held on March\xa05, 2024.\nOn\nMarch\xa05, 2024, the Board appointed Wendell E. Pritchett to serve as a member of the Board, the Audit Committee and the Nominating and Governance Committee, and as Chair of the Nominating and Governance Committee.\nDr.\xa0Pritchett will serve as a Class\xa0III Director of the Company, for a term that will expire at the Companys 2026 Annual Meeting of\nStockholders and until his successor is duly elected and qualified in accordance with the Companys organizational documents. The Board determined that Dr.\xa0Pritchett is not an interested person (as defined under\nSection\xa02(a)(19) of the Investment Company Act of 1940, as amended) of the Company or the Adviser, and meets the independence provisions promulgated by the SEC in Rule 10A-3 of the Exchange Act.\nThere are no arrangements or understandings between Dr.\xa0Pritchett and any other persons pursuant to which he was selected as a director. There are no\nfamily relationships between Dr.\xa0Pritchett and any director or executive officer of the Company. Other than as disclosed herein, Dr.\xa0Pritchett does not have any direct or indirect material interest in any transaction required to be\ndisclosed pursuant to Item 404(a) of Regulation S-K.\n126\nTable of Contents\nIn accordance with the compensation paid to Independent Directors of the Company, Dr.\xa0Pritchett will\nreceive an annual retainer of $70,000 for service on the Board and an additional annual retainer of $10,000 for service as the Chair of the Nominating and Governance Committee.\nIn connection with his appointment to the Board, Dr.\xa0Pritchett has entered into the Companys standard form of indemnification agreement for\ndirectors and officers.\nDr.\xa0Pritchett is the Riepe Presidential Professor of Law and Education at the University of Pennsylvania. Dr.\xa0Pritchett\nserved as the Interim President of the University of Pennsylvania from February 2022 to June 2022, and as the University Provost from 2017 to 2021. Dr.\xa0Pritchett first joined the University of Pennsylvania Carey Law School faculty in 2002 and\nserved as Interim Dean and Presidential Professor from 2014 to 2015 and as associate dean for academic affairs from 2006 to 2007. Dr.\xa0Pritchett also served as Chancellor of Rutgers-Camden from 2009 to 2014. During the past 15 years,\nDr.\xa0Pritchett has served in various leadership roles at nonprofit organizations. He has served as a member of the board of directors of Toll Brothers, Inc., a publicly traded real estate development company, since March 2018 and Clarivate plc,\na publicly traded information services company, since July 2022. Dr.\xa0Pritchett earned his Ph.D. in history from the University of Pennsylvania in 1997, a J.D. from Yale Law School in 1991 and a B.A. in political science from Brown University in\n1986.\nITEM\u20099C. Code on Google Colab#


You may visit this page - https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1BAWw3mCLQ7Rzuz8AYFzyTAFg9No-HEWC - to look at the codes for downloading the data minus the explanations found in this set of notes.






Making It Available#


We are going to download 5-year history worth of financial statements data for KO using Finance Toolkit and make it available on Google Sheets.






from financetoolkit import Toolkit

API_KEY = "*"
companies = Toolkit(['KO'], api_key=API_KEY, start_date="2017-12-31")

# Getting the balance sheet
bs = companies.get_balance_sheet_statement()[[str(i) for i in range(2019, 2024)]]
bs.to_csv('ko_bs_2023-2019_financetoolkit.csv')

# Getting the income statement
ics = companies.get_income_statement()
ics.to_csv('ko_ics_2023-2019_financetoolkit.csv')

# Getting the cash flow statement
cfs = companies.get_cash_flow_statement()
cfs.to_csv('ko_cfs_2023-2019_financetoolkit.csv')









Obtaining balance data: 100%|| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  8.84it/s]
Obtaining income data: 100%|| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  9.68it/s]
Obtaining cashflow data: 100%|| 1/1 [00:00<00:00,  9.42it/s]









The data is available at: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1OCqC9k0lz1kRZ-RXYRMgI8ebjHum1xHEfAYKl4t3Nos
